external_knowledge:
- "voyagers" refers to users navigating through episodes; 
- "explored more than one realm" indicates users who have accessed more than one episode;
- "bestowed upon each a golden star" means users have rated each episode they've accessed;
- "average sprinkle of stardust" metaphorically refers to the average rating given by the user;
- "shines brighter than the modest light of 8" implies the average rating is greater than 8.

sql:
SELECT episode_id, COUNT(rating_id) AS number_of_ratings
FROM episode_ratings
GROUP BY episode_id;
